data.label: Change project name in BuildTools
data.subText:
• Access the project in Build Tools 
  • Click on the upper right hand side cog to open settings, and click on Project Information
  • Change the job name from its default designation (-DSN) to reflect the contract type (e.g., 1A or 1B)
  • Change the status from DESIGN to CONSTRUCTION

data.label: Review all Project Checklists/Tasks in BT for each project you are the PM on and review Quality Control Checklists.
data.subText: ● Tasklist & QC Checklists

data.label: Upload Documents to BuildTools
data.subText:
• Access the DOCUMENTS module in Build tools
  • Upload the signed construction contract and the presentation into the 2-DESIGN folder 
  • The subfolder is Design + Budget Documents
  • Ensure all relevant people have access to the documents
  • Confirm that the uploaded documents are labeled appropriately for easy retrieval

data.label: Entering Payment Schedule into Financials in BuildTools
data.subText:
• Download the Contract from the DOCUMENTS module in Buildtools, and open up the page that has the PAYMENT SCHEDULE table embedded on it
  • In Buildtools, go to the FINANCIAL module on the left hand side
    • The project should already be turned off but double check so the client and team aren’t getting notifications for this portion
  • Click on the GREEN + button on the top header menu 
    • If a notification pops up about the budget, you can go ahead and JUST PUBLISH it under the title WORKING BUDGET
  • In the Title section - Put PAYMENT #(1,2,3) - CONTRACT ACCEPTANCE (or other milestone) as it appears in the payment schedule

  • Scroll down to DETAILS in the financial module and click on the 00 amount under CURRENT STATEMENT
  • Here you will enter the payment amount as it appears on the Payment Schedule
    • You can click tab or click out of it to enter it  - the percentage to the right will increase with each successful entrie
  • Repeat this process for all the payments
    • When you have successfully entered all payments, the percentage should be at 100%

data.label: Entering Allowances into Selections Module
data.subText:
• Open the exported Xactimate data in Excel and the Selections  BT Template 
  • Delete any existing data in the second tab, XACTIMATE (PASTE) and then copy the data from the Xactimate data and paste it into the worksheet
  • Filter out any blanks or items with no category - this will show only selection items
  • Remove columns that you aren’t going to need - it should look like this:

  • You will still need to filter out non-allowance items - you can use the FILTER function under the ITEM column an remove anything that says LABOR or INSTALL 
  • Under TYPE you need to make sure each row says SELECTION - you can type it in one and drag it down to the bottom of the list
  • In the NOTES column, you are going to put the allowance amount based on the QUANTITY, UNIT, and AMOUNT; For example:
  • finalize this checklist w correct process
